      • setOccupiedRegion

        protected void setOccupiedRegion​(java.lang.Object obj,
                                 Rect region,
                                 boolean revalidate)
        Sets an occupied region in the root layout widget. Border layouts will automatically attempt to deconflict with any occupied regions when the root layout is revalidated.

        This method may be used to either add or update a region associated with the specified object.

        Parameters:
        obj - The object that occupies the corresponding bounds
        region - The occupied region
        revalidate - If true, the layout will be revalidated before this method returns
